1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper deals with finding planar drawings of graphs of line or pseudoline arrangements, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. 
2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper mentions progress on the k-set problem from discrete geometry, indicating a connection to discrete mathematics. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper describes a linear-time algorithm for the problem, which is a key topic in data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper deals with drawing planar graphs, which is a topic in computer graphics. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper mentions the area complexity of the algorithm, which is a topic in computational complexity theory.
